  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes DF ATTY: Joseph R. Caton DF:  Sherlle Shameeka Williams appeared from jail. Case called at 2:15. Includes 15CF340, 15CF515. ADA Nieskes updates the court, there is an agreement.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads G to Ct 1 amending to a misdemeanor charge of theft in 15CF340 943.20(1)(a)(3)(a). DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1  in 15CF340 amending to a misdemeanor theft. On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses 15CF515. Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement. Crt orders:
- Costs to be converted to a civil judgment. 
- 20 days St. Croix County Jail
  Credit for time served. 
- Submit DNA sample and surcharge to be converted into a civil judgement.


DE is eligible for release today.
Filed by ADA Nieskes. km
